The paper discusses user authentication techniques, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper focuses on graphical user authentication, which involves the use of images and visual cues, making it relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also mentions the use of image processing techniques, which could fall under computer vision (cs.CV). The discussion of attack patterns and security standards could also make it relevant to cyber-physical systems (cs.CY) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
